Capacity sweep: k=5 polyphase (L=600) at WIDE channels=96 192 384. RF=125 sub-samples = 625 raw-ms (Δ+0.3% vs k=1). KEY EXPERIMENT — the apr25 k=5 collapse (+0.087) coincided with a 3.5× capacity drop vs baseline. If R² at WIDE recovers toward k=2 territory, the collapse was capacity-driven; if it stays near +0.10 the 200 Hz effective rate is the bottleneck and bigger models can't reconstruct missing temporal detail.